        <updateDate>2020-03-25T11:20:57Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Revamping American Infrastructure Act of 2020 </b></p> <p>This bill addresses the use of performance-based standards by the Department of Transportation (DOT).</p> <p>Specifically, DOT must</p> <ul> <li> invite the public to identify DOT regulations, guidance, and policies that establish prescriptive requirements for regulated entities that can be replaced with performance-based standards;</li> <li>submit and implement a plan to address feedback from the public that includes a detailed plan to replace the regulations, guidance, and policies with such standards; and</li> <li>ensure that its regulations, guidance, and policies issued are issued as performance-based standards.</li> </ul>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
